`pack --dry-run` on a pure-JS extension plans the official packer and surfaces the
official `<name>-<version>.ablx` filename, mutating nothing (DESIGN §2 pack, §4.7).

```
$ rackabel pack --dry-run
planned pack steps (nothing was changed):
  - production build (--release)
  - validate (manifest complete, minimumApiVersion <= host)
  - packer: official extensions-cli (pure-JS)
  - write [..]Clip-Renamer-0.1.0.ablx

```

`--no-official-cli --dry-run` switches to rackabel's own packer.

```
$ rackabel pack --no-official-cli --dry-run
planned pack steps (nothing was changed):
  - production build (--release)
  - validate (manifest complete, minimumApiVersion <= host)
  - packer: rackabel (--no-official-cli)
  - write [..].ablx [[..]]

```
